dev/plans/runs/12-DX-external-user-docs-output.json:67:  "loc_budget_note": "Spec budget was ~500-800 LoC of markdown. Actual additions land at ~1217 net new lines. Overshoot driven by 5 reference pages (python-api 167 + typescript-api 173 + cli 95 + errors 102 + config 81 = 618 LoC) which carry the locked-surface field-by-field documentation that clients need to actually use the SDKs. Each reference page is bounded (≤173 LoC) and cites the authoritative spec rather than duplicating it. Net-negative-LoC bias was applied to guides/operations (left as post-GA stubs) and to concepts/compatibility (60-100 LoC tight overview, not deep treatment). If orchestrator/reviewer wants the LoC under 800, candidates to trim are the worked-example block in errors.md and the per-step prose in quickstart.md, but neither is recommended — both serve concrete client utility.",
