     1	# Install — Python
     2	
     3	The `fathomdb` Python SDK is a [PyO3](https://pyo3.rs/) binding over the
     4	native Rust runtime. Wheels for the GA release will be platform-tagged
     5	(no source build required on supported platforms).
     6	
     7	## Requirements
     8	
     9	- Python **3.10**, **3.11**, or **3.12**
    10	- One of the supported platforms (per `release.yml` matrix):
    11	    - Linux `x86_64-unknown-linux-gnu` (manylinux 2_28)
    12	    - Linux `aarch64-unknown-linux-gnu` (manylinux 2_28)
    13	    - macOS `x86_64-apple-darwin`
    14	    - macOS `aarch64-apple-darwin`
    15	    - Windows `x86_64-pc-windows-msvc`
    16	- SQLite with the [`sqlite-vec`](https://github.com/asg017/sqlite-vec)
    17	  extension available to the loader (statically linked into the wheel
    18	  for supported platforms).
    19	
    20	## Install (post-GA)
    21	
    22	```bash
    23	pip install fathomdb==0.6.0
    24	```
    25	
    26	## Install (pre-GA, from source)
    27	
    28	`0.6.0` has not yet been published to PyPI. The current install path is
    29	editable from the `0.6.0-rewrite` branch using
    30	[maturin](https://www.maturin.rs/):
    31	
    32	```bash
    33	git clone https://github.com/coreyt/fathomdb
    34	cd fathomdb
    35	git checkout 0.6.0-rewrite
    36	pip install -e src/python/
    37	```
    38	
    39	`pip install -e src/python/` invokes maturin against the workspace and
    40	produces the native PyO3 extension `fathomdb._fathomdb`. **Do not run
    41	`cargo build` and copy the `.so` manually.** Editable install is the
    42	only supported native-build path for development.
    43	
    44	## Verify
    45	
    46	```python
    47	from fathomdb import Engine
    48	
    49	engine = Engine.open("./hello.fdb")
    50	engine.write([])
    51	engine.search("hello")
    52	engine.close()
    53	print("ok")
    54	```
    55	
    56	Expected output: `ok`. See [Quickstart](../getting-started/quickstart.md)
    57	for a richer walkthrough.
    58	
    59	## Troubleshooting
    60	
    61	- **`ImportError: libsqlite3 ...`** — your system SQLite is older than
    62	  the version the wheel was built against. Install via your package
    63	  manager (`apt install libsqlite3-dev`, `brew install sqlite`, etc.)
    64	  or upgrade.
    65	- **`OSError: sqlite-vec extension not found`** — `sqlite-vec` is
    66	  statically linked into the official wheels. If you are building from
    67	  source, ensure `sqlite-vec` is installed and discoverable by the
    68	  build script.
    69	- **`pip install -e src/python/` fails on `maturin`** — install maturin
    70	  explicitly (`pip install maturin`) and retry. The build also requires
    71	  a stable Rust toolchain (`rustup default stable`).
    72	- **`fathomdb.errors.DatabaseLockedError`** — another process holds an
    73	  exclusive lock on the DB file. See
    74	  [errors reference](../reference/errors.md).
    75	
    76	## See also
    77	
    78	- [Reference — Python API](../reference/python-api.md)
    79	- [Reference — config](../reference/config.md)
    80	- [Compatibility](../compatibility/index.md)
    81	- [Release notes — 0.6.0](../release-notes/0.6.0.md)

