     1	# Python API
     2	
     3	Module: `fathomdb`. Authoritative spec:
     4	[`dev/interfaces/python.md`](https://github.com/coreyt/fathomdb/blob/0.6.0-rewrite/dev/interfaces/python.md).
     5	
     6	## Top-level
     7	
     8	```python
     9	from fathomdb import (
    10	    Engine,
    11	    EngineConfig,
    12	    SearchResult,
    13	    SoftFallback,
    14	    SoftFallbackBranch,
    15	    WriteReceipt,
    16	    CounterSnapshot,
    17	    admin,
    18	    errors,
    19	)
    20	```
    21	
    22	## `Engine`
    23	
    24	### `Engine.open(path, *, config=None, **engine_config) -> Engine`
    25	
    26	Open or create a FathomDB database at `path`. Returns the engine
    27	handle.
    28	
    29	- `path` (`str`) — path to the SQLite DB file.
    30	- `config` (`EngineConfig | None`) — pre-built config object.
    31	- `**engine_config` — per-knob keyword arguments (see
    32	  [config](config.md)). Mutually exclusive with `config`.
    33	
    34	Raises `EngineError` subclasses on failure: `DatabaseLockedError`,
    35	`CorruptionError`, `IncompatibleSchemaVersionError`,
    36	`MigrationError`, `EmbedderIdentityMismatchError`,
    37	`EmbedderDimensionMismatchError`. See [errors](errors.md).
    38	
    39	> **0.6.0 caveat.** The PyO3 binding returns only the engine handle.
    40	> The structured open report
    41	> (`migration_version_reached`, `embedder_identity_confirmed`, open-
    42	> stage data) defined in `dev/design/engine.md` is populated on the
    43	> Rust side but dropped at the binding boundary. Surfacing it defers
    44	> to **0.6.1** (slice `12-TX-OPENREPORT`). Clients depending on
    45	> open-report data should pin to 0.6.1 when it ships. See
    46	> [release notes](../release-notes/0.6.0.md).
    47	
    48	### `engine.write(batch=None) -> WriteReceipt`
    49	
    50	Enqueue a batch of canonical rows. Synchronous; blocks until the
    51	writer thread has accepted the batch.
    52	
    53	- `batch` (`list[Any] | None`) — caller-shaped canonical rows.
    54	  Defaults to `[]`.
    55	- Returns: `WriteReceipt(cursor: int)`. The cursor advances
    56	  monotonically across writes.
    57	
    58	### `engine.search(query) -> SearchResult`
    59	
    60	Run hybrid retrieval (FTS5 + vector) for `query`.
    61	
    62	- `query` (`str`).
    63	- Returns: `SearchResult(projection_cursor: int, soft_fallback:
    64	  SoftFallback | None, results: list[str])`.
    65	
    66	### `engine.close() -> None`
    67	
    68	Release SQLite handles, join the writer thread, drain the scheduler,
    69	release the on-disk lock. Idempotent.
    70	
    71	### `engine.drain(*, timeout_s=0) -> None`
    72	
    73	Block until in-flight writes drain or `timeout_s` elapses. Argument
    74	unit is **seconds** (TS counterpart uses milliseconds).
    75	
    76	### `engine.counters() -> CounterSnapshot`
    77	
    78	Snapshot of engine-internal counters. See
    79	[`CounterSnapshot`](#countersnapshot) below.
    80	
    81	### `engine.set_profiling(*, enabled: bool) -> None`
    82	
    83	Toggle per-operation profiling.
    84	
    85	### `engine.set_slow_threshold_ms(*, value: int) -> None`
    86	
    87	Set the slow-query threshold for profiling event emission.
    88	
    89	### `engine.attach_logging_subscriber(logger, *, heartbeat_interval_ms=None) -> None`
    90	
    91	Bind engine events into a Python `logging.Logger`. Engine events are
    92	mapped to `logging.LogRecord` with the stable `fathomdb` payload.
    93	
    94	### Properties
    95	
    96	- `engine.path` (`str`) — DB path supplied to `open`.
    97	- `engine.config` (`EngineConfig`) — resolved config.
    98	
    99	## `admin.configure`
   100	
   101	```python
   102	from fathomdb import admin
   103	
   104	receipt = admin.configure(engine, name="my-schema", body=schema_json)
   105	```
   106	
   107	`admin.configure(engine, *, name: str, body: str) -> WriteReceipt`.
   108	
   109	Submit an admin schema configuration. The writer thread applies
   110	it; the returned cursor places the apply in the global write order.
   111	
   112	## Data shapes
   113	
   114	### `WriteReceipt`
   115	
   116	```python
   117	@dataclass(frozen=True)
   118	class WriteReceipt:
   119	    cursor: int
   120	```
   121	
   122	### `SearchResult`
   123	
   124	```python
   125	@dataclass(frozen=True)
   126	class SearchResult:
   127	    projection_cursor: int
   128	    soft_fallback: SoftFallback | None = None
   129	    results: list[str] = []
   130	```
   131	
   132	### `SoftFallback`
   133	
   134	```python
   135	@dataclass(frozen=True)
   136	class SoftFallback:
   137	    branch: SoftFallbackBranch  # Literal["vector", "text"]
   138	```
   139	
   140	`branch` indicates which non-essential branch could not contribute.
   141	Total request failure is not expressed via this carrier.
   142	
   143	### `CounterSnapshot`
   144	
   145	```python
   146	@dataclass(frozen=True)
   147	class CounterSnapshot:
   148	    queries: int = 0
   149	    writes: int = 0
   150	    write_rows: int = 0
   151	    admin_ops: int = 0
   152	    cache_hit: int = 0
   153	    cache_miss: int = 0
   154	```
   155	
   156	## Errors
   157	
   158	`fathomdb.errors` exports `EngineError` (the catch-all base) plus 18
   159	concrete leaf classes. See [errors reference](errors.md) for the full
   160	matrix and recovery-hint codes.
   161	
   162	## See also
   163	
   164	- [Quickstart](../getting-started/quickstart.md)
   165	- [Config knobs](config.md)
   166	- [Errors](errors.md)
   167	- Locked spec: [`dev/interfaces/python.md`](https://github.com/coreyt/fathomdb/blob/0.6.0-rewrite/dev/interfaces/python.md)

