    11	## Roots
    12	
    13	- `fathomdb doctor <verb> ...` — read-only or artifact-producing
    14	  diagnostics.
    15	- `fathomdb recover --accept-data-loss <sub-flag> ...` — the only
    16	  lossy / non-bit-preserving root.
    17	
    18	## Output
    19	
    20	- `--json` is the normative machine-readable contract on every verb.
    21	- `--pretty` is a human-only formatter on verbs that explicitly
    22	  document it.
    23	- `recover --json` emits an NDJSON progress stream plus a final
    24	  summary object. All other verbs emit a single JSON object.
    25	- Doctor wrap shape: `{ "verb": "<verb-name>", ...flattened_report_fields... }`.
    26	- Field names: serde `snake_case`.
    27	
    28	## Doctor verbs
    29	
    30	| Verb              | Synopsis                                                                       | Exit codes        |
    31	| ----------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------ | ----------------- |
    32	| `check-integrity` | `fathomdb doctor check-integrity [--quick] [--full] [--round-trip] [--pretty]` | `0` / `65` / `70` / `71` |
    33	| `safe-export`     | `fathomdb doctor safe-export <out> [--manifest <path>]`                        | `0` / `66` / `71` |
    34	| `verify-embedder` | `fathomdb doctor verify-embedder --identity <s> --dimension <n>`               | `0` / `65`        |
    35	| `trace`           | `fathomdb doctor trace --source-ref <id>`                                      | `0` / `65` / `70` / `71` |
    36	| `dump-schema`     | `fathomdb doctor dump-schema`                                                  | `0` / `65` / `70` / `71` |
    37	| `dump-row-counts` | `fathomdb doctor dump-row-counts`                                              | `0` / `65` / `70` / `71` |
    38	| `dump-profile`    | `fathomdb doctor dump-profile`                                                 | `0` / `65` / `70` / `71` |
    39	
    40	`check-integrity --full` may emit doctor-only finding codes such as
    41	`E_CORRUPT_INTEGRITY_CHECK`.
    42	
    43	## Recover root
    44	
    45	```text
    46	fathomdb recover --accept-data-loss
    47	  [--truncate-wal]
    48	  [--rebuild-vec0]
    49	  [--rebuild-projections]
    50	  [--excise-source <id>]
    51	```
    52	
    53	Exit codes: `0` / `64` / `70` / `71`.
    54	
    55	`--accept-data-loss` is declared on the `recover` parser only;
    56	`doctor` verbs reject it as unknown.
    57	
    58	`--rebuild-projections` is the canonical 0.6.0 regenerate workflow
    59	for failed or stale projections. There is no separate
    60	`fathomdb regenerate` command.
    61	
    62	### Client workaround — bulk delete by source
    63	
    64	Until logical-id verbs land in 0.7.x, the canonical 0.6.0 path for
    65	deleting all rows from a single ingestion source is:
    66	
    67	```bash
    68	fathomdb recover --accept-data-loss --excise-source <id> --json
    69	```
    70	
    71	## Exit-code classes
    72	
    73	| Code | Meaning                                                              |
    74	| ---- | -------------------------------------------------------------------- |
    75	| `0`  | successful completion; no findings requiring non-zero exit           |
    76	| `64` | recovery completed because lossy action was explicitly accepted      |
    77	| `65` | doctor / verification surface found actionable non-clean state       |
    78	| `66` | export / materialization failure on an artifact-producing doctor verb|
    79	| `70` | unrecoverable command failure                                        |
    80	| `71` | lock-held or equivalent precondition-blocked outcome                 |
    81	
    82	The full engine-error → exit-code mapping is in the locked spec.
    83	
    84	## Logical-id verbs (deferred)
    85	
    86	`purge_logical_id` and `restore_logical_id` are deferred to **0.7.x**
    87	(HITL re-confirmed 2026-05-17). The canonical-identity substrate is
    88	design-only in 0.6.0. See
    89	[release notes § Logical-id verbs](../release-notes/0.6.0.md).
    90	
    91	## See also
    92	
    93	- [Errors](errors.md)
    94	- [Install — Rust / CLI](../install/rust.md)
    95	- Locked spec: [`dev/interfaces/cli.md`](https://github.com/coreyt/fathomdb/blob/0.6.0-rewrite/dev/interfaces/cli.md)

