     1	# Errors
     2	
     3	Single-rooted exception hierarchy. Python root is `EngineError`; TS
     4	root is `FathomDbError`. Both bindings expose 1:1 the same 18 leaf
     5	classes (idiomatic spelling: Python snake_case payload fields, TS
     6	camelCase). Panic carriers are deliberately outside the catch-all
     7	root.
     8	
     9	Authoritative spec: [`dev/design/errors.md`](https://github.com/coreyt/fathomdb/blob/0.6.0-rewrite/dev/design/errors.md).
    10	
    11	## Catch-all base
    12	
    13	| Binding    | Class            | Module                |
    14	| ---------- | ---------------- | --------------------- |
    15	| Python     | `EngineError`    | `fathomdb.errors`     |
    16	| TypeScript | `FathomDbError`  | `fathomdb` (top-level)|
    17	
    18	Catch-all examples:
    19	
    20	```python
    21	from fathomdb.errors import EngineError
    22	try:
    23	    engine.write([...])
    24	except EngineError as e:
    25	    log.exception("fathomdb call failed", exc_info=e)
    26	```
    27	
    28	```ts
    29	import { FathomDbError } from "fathomdb";
    30	try {
    31	  await engine.write([...]);
    32	} catch (e) {
    33	  if (e instanceof FathomDbError) { /* ... */ }
    34	  throw e;
    35	}
    36	```
    37	
    38	## Leaf class matrix
    39	
    40	| Class                              | Trigger                                                                       | Typed payload (Py / TS)                                                  | Recovery hint           |
    41	| ---------------------------------- | ----------------------------------------------------------------------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------------------ | ----------------------- |
    42	| `StorageError`                     | SQLite-layer fault on a non-corruption path                                   | —                                                                        | retry; if persistent, run `doctor check-integrity` |
    43	| `ProjectionError`                  | Projection apply fault                                                        | —                                                                        | run `doctor check-integrity --full`; recover with `--rebuild-projections` |
    44	| `VectorError`                      | `sqlite-vec` fault                                                            | —                                                                        | run `doctor check-integrity`; recover with `--rebuild-vec0` |
    45	| `EmbedderError`                    | Embedder call failed                                                          | —                                                                        | check embedder process / timeout; see `embedder_call_timeout_ms` |
    46	| `EmbedderNotConfiguredError`       | Vector op attempted with no embedder configured                               | —                                                                        | configure an embedder via `admin.configure` |
    47	| `KindNotVectorIndexedError`        | Vector op attempted on a kind that has no vector projection                   | —                                                                        | add vector projection in schema |
    48	| `SchedulerError`                   | Background scheduler fault                                                    | —                                                                        | retry; on persistent failure, restart process |
    49	| `OpStoreError`                     | Op-store (write log) fault                                                    | —                                                                        | run `doctor check-integrity --full` |
    50	| `WriteValidationError`             | Caller-supplied write batch failed validation                                 | —                                                                        | fix the batch; check schema |
    51	| `SchemaValidationError`            | Admin schema configuration failed validation                                  | —                                                                        | fix the schema |
    52	| `OverloadedError`                  | Backpressure: queue full                                                      | —                                                                        | slow producers; raise `embedder_pool_size` or `scheduler_runtime_threads` |
    53	| `ClosingError`                     | Operation issued while engine is closing                                      | —                                                                        | do not reuse a closed engine |
    54	| `DatabaseLockedError`              | On-disk lock held by another process                                          | `holder_pid` / `holderPid`                                               | wait for holder to release, or kill it |
    55	| `CorruptionError`                  | Open-time integrity failure                                                   | `kind`, `stage`, `recovery_hint_code` / camelCase + `doc_anchor`         | follow `recovery_hint_code`; see `doctor` + `recover` |
    56	| `IncompatibleSchemaVersionError`   | DB on-disk schema not compatible with this build                              | —                                                                        | upgrade engine; or downgrade DB                                |
    57	| `MigrationError`                   | Migration step failed                                                         | —                                                                        | see `doctor check-integrity`; may require `recover` |
    58	| `EmbedderIdentityMismatchError`    | Configured embedder identity differs from stored                              | `stored_name`, `stored_revision`, `supplied_name`, `supplied_revision`   | restore prior embedder OR re-embed with new identity |
    59	| `EmbedderDimensionMismatchError`   | Configured embedder dimension differs from stored                             | `stored`, `supplied`                                                     | restore prior dimension OR re-embed |
    60	
    61	## Recovery hint codes
    62	
    63	`CorruptionError.recovery_hint_code` is a stable string identifier
    64	(e.g. `E_CORRUPT_INTEGRITY_CHECK`) keyed in `dev/design/errors.md`.
    65	Operators dispatch on the code, not the message.
    66	
    67	## Panic carriers
    68	
    69	Rust runtime panics surface as:
    70	
    71	- Python: `pyo3_runtime.PanicException` (PyO3-owned; **not**
    72	  `EngineError`).
    73	- TypeScript: `FathomDbPanicError` (TS-owned; **not** `FathomDbError`).
    74	
    75	Panics indicate a contract bug. They are deliberately outside the
    76	catch-all root so `except EngineError` / `catch FathomDbError` does
    77	not silently swallow them.
    78	
    79	## Worked example — corruption recovery
    80	
    81	```python
    82	from fathomdb import Engine
    83	from fathomdb.errors import CorruptionError
    84	
    85	try:
    86	    engine = Engine.open("./mydb.fdb")
    87	except CorruptionError as e:
    88	    print("kind:", e.kind)
    89	    print("stage:", e.stage)
    90	    print("hint:", e.recovery_hint_code)
    91	    # operator path: see CLI reference
    92	    # fathomdb doctor check-integrity --full --json
    93	    # fathomdb recover --accept-data-loss --rebuild-vec0 --json
    94	    raise
    95	```
    96	
    97	## See also
    98	
    99	- [Python API](python-api.md)
   100	- [TypeScript API](typescript-api.md)
   101	- [CLI](cli.md)
   102	- Authoritative spec: [`dev/design/errors.md`](https://github.com/coreyt/fathomdb/blob/0.6.0-rewrite/dev/design/errors.md)

