     1	# Config
     2	
     3	Engine-owned runtime knobs. The same five knobs are exposed by every
     4	binding in idiomatic spelling (Python snake_case, TS camelCase, Rust
     5	snake_case).
     6	
     7	Authoritative spec: [`dev/design/engine.md`](https://github.com/coreyt/fathomdb/blob/0.6.0-rewrite/dev/design/engine.md);
     8	cross-binding symmetry pinned by `dev/design/bindings.md` § 6.
     9	
    10	## Knob matrix
    11	
    12	| Knob                          | Python                     | TypeScript                | Type             | Notes                                                                |
    13	| ----------------------------- | -------------------------- | ------------------------- | ---------------- | -------------------------------------------------------------------- |
    14	| Embedder pool size            | `embedder_pool_size`       | `embedderPoolSize`        | `int \| None`    | Max concurrent embedder calls. `None` = engine default.              |
    15	| Scheduler runtime threads     | `scheduler_runtime_threads`| `schedulerRuntimeThreads` | `int \| None`    | Threads in the scheduler runtime. `None` = engine default.           |
    16	| Provenance row cap            | `provenance_row_cap`       | `provenanceRowCap`        | `int \| None`    | Max provenance rows retained.                                        |
    17	| Embedder call timeout (ms)    | `embedder_call_timeout_ms` | `embedderCallTimeoutMs`   | `int \| None`    | Per-call timeout for embedder invocations.                           |
    18	| Slow query threshold (ms)     | `slow_threshold_ms`        | `slowThresholdMs`         | `int \| None`    | Profiling event emission threshold. Mutable via `set_slow_threshold_ms`. |
    19	
    20	`None` (Python) / `undefined` (TS) → engine default. Defaults are
    21	internal-tunable; callers should not depend on specific numeric
    22	defaults.
    23	
    24	## Python — two equivalent forms
    25	
    26	Object form:
    27	
    28	```python
    29	from fathomdb import Engine, EngineConfig
    30	
    31	config = EngineConfig(embedder_pool_size=4, slow_threshold_ms=200)
    32	engine = Engine.open("./mydb.fdb", config=config)
    33	```
    34	
    35	Keyword form:
    36	
    37	```python
    38	engine = Engine.open(
    39	    "./mydb.fdb",
    40	    embedder_pool_size=4,
    41	    slow_threshold_ms=200,
    42	)
    43	```
    44	
    45	The two forms are mutually exclusive within a single `Engine.open`
    46	call. Unknown keyword arguments are rejected with `TypeError`.
    47	
    48	## TypeScript
    49	
    50	```ts
    51	import { Engine } from "fathomdb";
    52	
    53	const engine = await Engine.open("./mydb.fdb", {
    54	  engineConfig: {
    55	    embedderPoolSize: 4,
    56	    slowThresholdMs: 200,
    57	  },
    58	});
    59	```
    60	
    61	`EngineOpenOptions` may carry a TS-binding-specific
    62	ThreadsafeFunction handoff-pool sizing option **beside** `engineConfig`.
    63	That option is a TS-runtime concern, not a canonical engine config
    64	field, and has no Python counterpart by design.
    65	
    66	## Non-fields
    67	
    68	Python executor usage is caller-owned and is not an engine config
    69	field. Path is positional on `Engine.open` and is not a config field.
    70	
    71	## Mutable-at-runtime
    72	
    73	Only `slow_threshold_ms` / `slowThresholdMs` is mutable post-open via
    74	`engine.set_slow_threshold_ms` / `engine.setSlowThresholdMs`. All
    75	other knobs are open-time only.
    76	
    77	## See also
    78	
    79	- [Python API — Engine.open](python-api.md)
    80	- [TypeScript API — Engine.open](typescript-api.md)
    81	- Authoritative spec: [`dev/design/engine.md`](https://github.com/coreyt/fathomdb/blob/0.6.0-rewrite/dev/design/engine.md)

