     1	# Compatibility
     2	
     3	Supported platforms, toolchains, and version-alignment policy for
     4	the 0.6.0 release.
     5	
     6	## Supported Python versions
     7	
     8	`3.10`, `3.11`, `3.12`. Wheels published for each via the
     9	`release.yml` `build-python` matrix.
    10	
    11	## Supported Node versions
    12	
    13	Node **18** or later. CI runs on Node **22**.
    14	
    15	## Supported Rust toolchain
    16	
    17	Rust **stable**. Specific minimum-supported-rust-version is pinned at
    18	release time; the `release.yml` toolchain step uses `dtolnay/rust-toolchain@stable`.
    19	
    20	## Supported platforms
    21	
    22	Same matrix across Python wheels, napi `.node` binaries, and Rust
    23	crates (per `release.yml`):
    24	
    25	| OS      | Architecture           |
    26	| ------- | ---------------------- |
    27	| Linux   | `x86_64-unknown-linux-gnu`  |
    28	| Linux   | `aarch64-unknown-linux-gnu` |
    29	| macOS   | `x86_64-apple-darwin`       |
    30	| macOS   | `aarch64-apple-darwin`      |
    31	| Windows | `x86_64-pc-windows-msvc`    |
    32	
    33	Linux wheels are manylinux 2_28. Other platforms outside this matrix
    34	are unsupported in 0.6.0.
    35	
    36	## SQLite + sqlite-vec
    37	
    38	- Engine uses SQLite **FTS5** + the
    39	  [`sqlite-vec`](https://github.com/asg017/sqlite-vec) extension.
    40	- Wheels and platform `.node` binaries statically link a compatible
    41	  build of `sqlite-vec`.
    42	- Rust + source-build users need a working SQLite + `sqlite-vec`
    43	  available to the loader.
    44	
    45	## Versioning — two axes
    46	
    47	`0.6.0` follows two-axis versioning:
    48	
    49	- **Axis W (workspace lockstep)** — the six runtime / binding / CLI
    50	  crates plus the Python and TypeScript packages all carry the same
    51	  workspace version. `scripts/set-version.sh --check-files` enforces
    52	  this pre-publish; the pre-push hook runs the check.
    53	- **Axis E (`fathomdb-embedder-api`)** — the embedder-trait crate is
    54	  versioned independently per
    55	  `ADR-0.6.0-embedder-protocol`. Bumping a binding does not force an
    56	  embedder-api bump.
    57	
    58	This decouples embedder-protocol stability from binding cadence.
    59	
    60	## 0.5.x compatibility
    61	
    62	**No 0.5.x compatibility shims or migrations.** 0.6.0 is a rewrite.
    63	Clients on 0.5.x follow a separate migration guide (not provided in
    64	0.6.0). Do not point 0.6.0 binaries at 0.5.x databases.
    65	
    66	## Performance posture — deferred gates
    67	
    68	Four performance ACs are deferred for 0.6.0 (HITL re-confirmed
    69	2026-05-17 per Phase 12-P decision). Clients evaluating fathomdb for
    70	perf-sensitive workloads should plan accordingly:
    71	
    72	| AC      | Surface                          | Closure target |
    73	| ------- | -------------------------------- | -------------- |
    74	| AC-012  | text query latency on FTS5 (p50 ≤ 20 ms / p99 ≤ 150 ms) | 0.6.1 (canonical-runner re-measurement) |
    75	| AC-013  | vector retrieval latency (p50 ≤ 50 ms / p99 ≤ 200 ms)   | Pack 7 (batched-insert vec0)            |
    76	| AC-019  | mixed-retrieval stress tail                             | Pack 7 (inherits AC-013)                |
    77	| AC-020  | N=8 concurrent reader scaling (architectural gap)       | Pack 7 vendor-SQLite work                |
    78	
    79	Engine surfaces these as documented gates, not weakened ones. See
    80	`dev/test-plan.md` § Current Perf Attribution and
    81	[release notes — 0.6.0 § Performance gates](../release-notes/0.6.0.md).
    82	
    83	## API surface deferrals
    84	
    85	- `Engine.open` structured open report dropped by both bindings;
    86	  surfacing defers to 0.6.1 (slice `12-TX-OPENREPORT`).
    87	- Logical-id verbs (`purge_logical_id`, `restore_logical_id`)
    88	  deferred to 0.7.x.
    89	
    90	See [release notes — 0.6.0](../release-notes/0.6.0.md) for the full
    91	deferred-items disclosure.

