     1	# Concepts
     2	
     3	Mental model for the 0.6.0 public surface. Detailed treatment lives
     4	in internal design docs under
     5	[`dev/design/`](https://github.com/coreyt/fathomdb/tree/0.6.0-rewrite/dev/design);
     6	this page is the consumer-facing overview.
     7	
     8	## Engine lifecycle
     9	
    10	```text
    11	open → write / search / admin.configure / instrumentation → close → process exit
    12	```
    13	
    14	1. **Open** — `Engine.open(path)` creates or opens the SQLite database
    15	   at `path`. The handle owns the writer thread, the reader pool with
    16	   thread-affine workers, the scheduler, the op-store, and the
    17	   embedder pool. Open is the only place migration runs.
    18	2. **Write / search / configure** — application code calls the
    19	   five-verb canonical surface. Writes are serialized through the
    20	   writer thread; reads are served by the reader pool; admin
    21	   configurations apply in write order.
    22	3. **Close** — `engine.close()` joins the writer thread, drains the
    23	   scheduler, releases SQLite handles, and releases the on-disk lock.
    24	   Idempotent.
    25	4. **Process exit** — the process must exit cleanly after close. The
    26	   wheel-on-disk lock cleanup and process exit are the bug signal the
    27	   release smokes watch for (per `feedback_release_verification`).
    28	
    29	## Five-verb runtime surface
    30	
    31	The canonical surface across every binding:
    32	
    33	- `Engine.open(path, **config)` — open or create a DB.
    34	- `engine.write(batch)` — enqueue canonical rows.
    35	- `engine.search(query)` — hybrid retrieval (FTS5 + vector).
    36	- `engine.close()` — release resources.
    37	- `admin.configure(engine, name=..., body=...)` — apply a schema /
    38	  embedder / projection configuration.
    39	
    40	Engine-attached instrumentation (`drain`, `counters`,
    41	`set_profiling`, `set_slow_threshold_ms`, subscriber attach) is not
    42	an additional top-level verb; it is a method namespace on the
    43	`Engine` handle.
    44	
    45	## Canonical rows and projections
    46	
    47	- **Canonical rows** are the durable ground-truth writes the client
    48	  enqueues via `engine.write`. They are the source of truth and are
    49	  bit-preservable across recovery actions other than explicit
    50	  data-loss steps.
    51	- **Projections** are engine-maintained derived state computed off the
    52	  canonical row stream — FTS5 indexes, `sqlite-vec` vector indexes,
    53	  and other shape-specific materializations. Projections are
    54	  rebuildable from canonical rows via
    55	  `fathomdb recover --accept-data-loss --rebuild-projections` (or
    56	  `--rebuild-vec0` for the vector subset).
    57	
    58	## Embedder model
    59	
    60	Embedders are pluggable components that produce vector embeddings
    61	for vector-indexed kinds. The trait surface lives in
    62	`fathomdb-embedder-api` (Axis E — see
    63	[compatibility § versioning](../compatibility/index.md)), and is
    64	configured via `admin.configure`. Embedder identity (`name` +
    65	`revision`) and `dimension` are stored on first configure; an attempt
    66	to re-open with a different embedder raises
    67	`EmbedderIdentityMismatchError` or `EmbedderDimensionMismatchError`.
    68	
    69	Vector identity belongs to the embedder per `ADR-0.6.0-vector-identity-embedder-owned`.
    70	
    71	Detailed trait + lifecycle docs: see Rust API docs (`docs.rs/fathomdb-embedder-api` post-publish; pre-GA, see
    72	[`src/rust/crates/fathomdb-embedder-api/`](https://github.com/coreyt/fathomdb/tree/0.6.0-rewrite/src/rust/crates/fathomdb-embedder-api)).
    73	
    74	## Recovery surface
    75	
    76	The CLI exposes two roots:
    77	
    78	- `fathomdb doctor <verb>` — read-only or artifact-producing
    79	  diagnostics. `check-integrity`, `safe-export`, `verify-embedder`,
    80	  `trace`, `dump-schema`, `dump-row-counts`, `dump-profile`.
    81	- `fathomdb recover --accept-data-loss <sub-flag>` — the only lossy
    82	  root. `--truncate-wal`, `--rebuild-vec0`, `--rebuild-projections`,
    83	  `--excise-source <id>`.
    84	
    85	Engine errors from the SDK carry recovery hints (notably
    86	`CorruptionError.recovery_hint_code`); operators dispatch on the
    87	hint code, not the message.
    88	
    89	The CLI is **operator-only** in 0.6.0 — it does not mirror the SDK
    90	five-verb application surface. There is no `fathomdb search` /
    91	`get` / `list`.
    92	
    93	Logical-id verbs (`purge_logical_id`, `restore_logical_id`) are
    94	deferred to 0.7.x; bulk-delete-by-source for 0.6.0 uses
    95	`fathomdb recover --accept-data-loss --excise-source <id>`.
    96	
    97	## See also
    98	
    99	- [Quickstart](../getting-started/quickstart.md)
   100	- [Reference — Errors](../reference/errors.md)
   101	- [Reference — CLI](../reference/cli.md)
   102	- [Compatibility](../compatibility/index.md)

