     9	
    10	# CLI Interface
    11	
    12	Public CLI surface for the 0.6.0 operator binary. The canonical verb table and
    13	recovery semantics are owned by `design/recovery.md`; this file owns concrete
    14	flag spelling, root command paths, and exit-code classes.
    15	
    16	## Roots
    17	
    18	- `fathomdb recover --accept-data-loss <sub-flag>...`
    19	- `fathomdb doctor <verb> ...`
    20	
    21	The CLI is **operator-only** in 0.6.0. It does not mirror the SDK five-verb
    22	application surface and does not ship `search` / `get` / `list` query verbs.
    23	
    24	## Output posture
    25	
    26	- `--json` is the normative machine-readable contract on every verb.
    27	- `doctor check-integrity` emits a single JSON object.
    28	- `doctor check-integrity --full` may emit doctor-only finding codes such as
    29	  `E_CORRUPT_INTEGRITY_CHECK`.
    30	- `recover` JSON output is a progress stream plus summary, owned by
    31	  `design/recovery.md`.
    32	- `--pretty` is a human-only formatter on verbs that explicitly document it;
    33	  it is not a separate machine schema.
    34	
    35	## Exit-code classes
    36	
    37	| Code | Stable meaning                                                       | Primary owner                    |
    38	| ---- | -------------------------------------------------------------------- | -------------------------------- |
    39	| `0`  | successful completion with no findings that require a non-zero exit  | this file                        |
    40	| `64` | recovery completed only because lossy action was explicitly accepted | this file + `design/recovery.md` |
    41	| `65` | doctor/verification surface found actionable non-clean state         | this file + `design/recovery.md` |
    42	| `66` | export/materialization failure on an artifact-producing doctor verb  | this file + `design/recovery.md` |
    43	| `70` | unrecoverable command failure                                        | this file                        |
    44	| `71` | lock-held or equivalent precondition-blocked outcome                 | this file + `design/bindings.md` |
    45	
    46	## Doctor verbs
    47	
    48	| Verb              | Synopsis                                                                       | Exit class                          |
    49	| ----------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------ | ----------------------------------- |
    50	| `check-integrity` | `fathomdb doctor check-integrity [--quick] [--full] [--round-trip] [--pretty]` | `doctor-check-*` = 0 / 65 / 70 / 71 |
    51	| `safe-export`     | `fathomdb doctor safe-export <out> [--manifest <path>]`                        | `doctor-export-*` = 0 / 66 / 71     |
    52	| `verify-embedder` | `fathomdb doctor verify-embedder --identity <s> --dimension <n>`               | `doctor-check-*` = 0 / 65           |
    53	| `trace`           | `fathomdb doctor trace --source-ref <id>`                                      | `doctor-check-*`                    |
    54	| `dump-schema`     | `fathomdb doctor dump-schema`                                                  | `doctor-check-*`                    |
    55	| `dump-row-counts` | `fathomdb doctor dump-row-counts`                                              | `doctor-check-*`                    |
    56	| `dump-profile`    | `fathomdb doctor dump-profile`                                                 | `doctor-check-*`                    |
    57	
    58	`doctor-check-*` means the verb may use the exit-code class set `{0, 65, 70,
    59	71}` depending on clean/findings/unrecoverable/lock-held outcome.
    60	
    61	## Recover root
    62	
    63	`recover` is the only lossy / non-bit-preserving root in 0.6.0.
    64	
    65	```text
    66	fathomdb recover --accept-data-loss
    67	  [--truncate-wal]
    68	  [--rebuild-vec0]
    69	  [--rebuild-projections]
    70	  [--excise-source <id>]
    71	```
    72	
    73	Exit class: `recover-*` = 0 / 64 / 70 / 71.
    74	
    75	`--accept-data-loss` is declared on the `recover` parser only. `doctor` verbs
    76	reject it as unknown.
    77	
    78	`--rebuild-projections` is the canonical 0.6.0 regenerate workflow for failed
    79	or stale projections. The docs may refer to "regenerate" as the workflow name,
    80	but there is no separate `fathomdb regenerate` command in 0.6.0.
    81	
    82	## Error to exit-code mapping
    83	
    84	The CLI dispatcher translates engine error variants (and CLI-detected
    85	preconditions) to the exit-code classes above. This table binds each variant
    86	to its class.
    87	
    88	| Source error variant                             | Exit code | Class         |
    89	| ------------------------------------------------ | --------- | ------------- |
    90	| (clean completion)                               | 0         | success       |
    91	| recover sub-action gated by `--accept-data-loss` | 64        | data-loss-ack |
    92	| `doctor check-integrity` findings non-empty      | 65        | findings      |
    93	| `doctor safe-export` failed manifest/export step | 66        | artifact-fail |
    94	| `EngineError::Storage`                           | 70        | unrecoverable |
    95	| `EngineError::Projection`                        | 70        | unrecoverable |
    96	| `EngineError::Vector`                            | 70        | unrecoverable |
    97	| `EngineError::Embedder`                          | 70        | unrecoverable |
    98	| `EngineError::Scheduler`                         | 70        | unrecoverable |
    99	| `EngineError::OpStore`                           | 70        | unrecoverable |
   100	| `EngineError::Overloaded`                        | 70        | unrecoverable |
   101	| `EngineError::SchemaValidation`                  | 70        | unrecoverable |
   102	| `EngineError::WriteValidation`                   | 70        | unrecoverable |
   103	| `EngineError::EmbedderNotConfigured`             | 70        | unrecoverable |
   104	| `EngineError::KindNotVectorIndexed`              | 70        | unrecoverable |
   105	| `EngineError::EmbedderDimensionMismatch{..}`     | 70        | unrecoverable |
   106	| `EngineOpenError::DatabaseLocked{..}`            | 71        | lock-held     |
   107	| `EngineError::Closing`                           | 71        | lock-held     |
   108	| `EngineOpenError::Corruption(..)`                | 70        | unrecoverable |
   109	| `EngineOpenError::IncompatibleSchemaVersion{..}` | 70        | unrecoverable |
   110	| `EngineOpenError::MigrationError{..}`            | 70        | unrecoverable |
   111	| `EngineOpenError::EmbedderIdentityMismatch{..}`  | 70        | unrecoverable |
   112	| `EngineOpenError::EmbedderDimensionMismatch{..}` | 70        | unrecoverable |
   113	| `EngineOpenError::Io{..}`                        | 70        | unrecoverable |
   114	
   115	## JSON output wrapping
   116	
   117	`fathomdb-cli` owns top-level discriminator wrapping. The engine returns
   118	typed report structs; the CLI serializes them under a `verb` discriminator.
   119	
   120	- All `--json` output is one JSON object (or an NDJSON stream for `recover`).
   121	- Doctor verb wrapping pattern: `{ "verb": "<verb-name>", ...flattened_engine_report_fields... }`.
   122	- Non-flat reports nest naturally. For example, `IntegrityReport` serializes
   123	  as `{ "verb": "check-integrity", "physical": {...}, "logical": {...}, "semantic": {...} }`.
   124	- Field name policy: serde default `snake_case`. Any divergence from engine
   125	  field spellings lives in the CLI serialization layer; the engine report
   126	  structs are not renamed to satisfy CLI spelling requirements.

