     1	# 0.6.0 Release Notes (Preview)
     2	
     3	**Status: pre-release.** `0.6.0` is on the `0.6.0-rewrite` branch
     4	and has not yet been published to crates.io / PyPI / npm. This
     5	page previews what 0.6.0 will deliver when the GA tag fires.
     6	
     7	## What 0.6.0 delivers
     8	
     9	### Engine + storage substrate
    10	
    11	- Local-first retrieval engine on SQLite (FTS5 + `sqlite-vec`).
    12	- Canonical writes, vector projections, scheduler, op-store,
    13	  reader pool with thread-affine workers.
    14	- Typed error hierarchy: `EngineError` plus structured leaves
    15	  (`StorageError`, `ProjectionError`, `VectorError`,
    16	  `EmbedderError`, `EmbedderNotConfiguredError`,
    17	  `KindNotVectorIndexedError`, `SchedulerError`, `OpStoreError`,
    18	  `WriteValidationError`, `SchemaValidationError`,
    19	  `OverloadedError`, `ClosingError`, `DatabaseLockedError`,
    20	  `CorruptionError`, `IncompatibleSchemaVersionError`).
    21	- Five-verb runtime SDK surface: `Engine.open`, `engine.write`,
    22	  `engine.search`, `engine.close`, `admin.configure`.
    23	- Engine-attached instrumentation: `engine.drain`,
    24	  `engine.counters`, `engine.set_profiling`,
    25	  `engine.set_slow_threshold_ms`, host logging subscriber attach.
    26	
    27	### Bindings
    28	
    29	- **Python SDK** (`fathomdb`) — PyO3 binding. Type stubs at
    30	  `fathomdb/_fathomdb.pyi`. Public surface locked at
    31	  `dev/interfaces/python.md` (internal spec).
    32	- **TypeScript SDK** (`fathomdb`) — napi-rs binding. Promise API,
    33	  handoff pool, typed exception envelope.
    34	- **Rust facade crate** (`fathomdb`) — re-exports the runtime
    35	  verbs from `fathomdb-engine` for downstream Rust consumers.
    36	- **CLI** (`fathomdb-cli`) — `doctor` and `recover` verbs
    37	  (Phase 10a). Logical-id verbs deferred to 0.7.x — see below.
    38	
    39	### Release engineering
    40	
    41	- Two-axis versioning: Axis W (workspace lockstep across the
    42	  six runtime/binding/CLI crates + Python + TS packages); Axis E
    43	  (`fathomdb-embedder-api` independent — trait surface stability
    44	  per ADR-0.6.0-embedder-protocol).
    45	- 8-tier topological publish order via `.github/workflows/release.yml`
    46	  with crates.io index-propagation sleeps between tiers and
    47	  post-publish smoke against fresh installs from each registry.
    48	- Single brand: `fathomdb` on crates.io / PyPI / npm.
    49	- `scripts/set-version.sh --check-files` enforces axis lockstep
    50	  pre-publish; pre-push hook runs the check before agent-verify.
    51	- actionlint v1.7.7 wired as canonical workflow validator.
    52	
    53	## What is deferred (will not ship in 0.6.0 GA)
    54	
    55	These are documented and will appear in the final GA release
    56	notes verbatim.
    57	
    58	### Performance gates (4 ACs)
    59	
    60	Performance acceptance criteria **AC-012**, **AC-013**, **AC-019**,
    61	**AC-020** are deferred for 0.6.0 (HITL re-confirmed 2026-05-17
    62	per Phase 12-P decision). Engine surfaces them as documented gates,
    63	not weakened ones. See `dev/test-plan.md` § Current Perf Attribution
    64	for the canonical rationale and Pack 7 remediation track.
    65	
    66	- **AC-012** text query latency on FTS5 (p50 ≤ 20 ms / p99 ≤ 150 ms):
    67	  closes in **0.6.1** via canonical-runner re-measurement (dev
    68	  runner is aarch64 Tegra ~3× slower than canonical x86_64). No
    69	  engine code change expected.
    70	- **AC-013** vector retrieval latency (p50 ≤ 50 ms / p99 ≤ 200 ms):
    71	  closes via **Pack 7** batched-insert vec0 API (current bulk-seed
    72	  is engine-surface gap, not retrieval-path issue).
    73	- **AC-019** mixed-retrieval stress tail: closes via Pack 7
    74	  (inherits AC-013 substrate).
    75	- **AC-020** N=8 concurrent reader scaling: **architectural gap**.
    76	  Best speedup on dev runner 3.53× vs required ≥ 5.33×; residual
    77	  is `pcache1` mutex acquires on every page-fetch (hit-path).
    78	  Closure requires Pack 7 vendor-SQLite work
    79	  (`SQLITE_CONFIG_PCACHE2` custom allocator OR WAL2 OR
    80	  reader/writer physical separation OR vendor-SQLite swap). Pack
    81	  5 + Pack 6 + Pack 6.G falsified every canonical-SQLite lever
    82	  measurable on the AC-020 fixture.
    83	
    84	### `Engine.open` structured open report
    85	
    86	Both Python and TypeScript SDKs currently return only the engine handle
    87	from `Engine.open`. The structured open report (migration-version-
    88	reached, embedder-identity-confirmed, open-stage data) defined in
    89	`design/engine.md` and called for by `interfaces/{python,typescript}.md`
    90	is populated on the native Rust side (`OpenedEngine.report`) but
    91	**dropped by both bindings in 0.6.0**.
    92	
    93	Surfacing the open report defers to **0.6.1** (slice
    94	`12-TX-OPENREPORT`). Symmetric across both bindings, so not a
    95	TS-vs-Python parity gap. Clients depending on open-report data
    96	should pin to 0.6.1 when it ships.
    97	
    98	### Logical-id verbs
    99	
   100	`purge_logical_id` and `restore_logical_id` deferred to **0.7.x**
   101	(HITL re-confirmed 2026-05-17 per Phase 12-V-VERBS decision). The
   102	canonical-identity substrate (`row_id` / `logical_id` /
   103	`superseded_at` / `restore_provenance` columns, partial unique
   104	index on `(logical_id, kind)`, writer supersession step) is
   105	design-only in 0.6.0 — verbs cannot be built without the substrate.
   106	
   107	**Client workaround for 0.6.0**: bulk-delete by source uses
   108	`fathomdb recover --excise-source <id>` (landed in Phase 10a).
   109	Restore-from-log workflows wait for 0.7.x.
   110	
   111	See `dev/design/recovery.md` § Logical-id purge and restore for
   112	the design + substrate spec.
   113	
   114	### TypeScript SDK parity
   115	
   116	- TS milestone 1 shipped 2026-04-07; not yet feature-equal with
   117	  Python. TS Python-parity is a Phase 12 deliverable (will close
   118	  before GA tag) but lands after performance + security + verb
   119	  decisions. Until then, prefer the Python SDK for production
   120	  pilots.
   121	
   122	### Compatibility
   123	
   124	- **No 0.5.x compatibility shims or migrations.** 0.6.0 is a
   125	  rewrite; clients on 0.5.x must follow a separate migration
   126	  guide (not provided in 0.6.0).
   127	
   128	## How to follow along
   129	
   130	- Plan + status: `dev/plans/0.6.0-implementation.md` § Path to
   131	  Client-Ready (0.6.0 GA).
   132	- Public interface specs (internal-facing):
   133	  `dev/interfaces/{rust,python,typescript,cli,wire}.md`.
   134	- Acceptance scoreboard: `dev/acceptance.md`.
   135	
   136	When 0.6.0 GA tags, this page will be replaced with the final
   137	release notes including install commands for all three registries.

